net.truelicense.api

Interface LicenseKeyGenerator

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    UncheckedLicenseKeyGenerator

    public interface LicenseKeyGenerator
    Generates a license key and writes it to a given sink or returns a duplicate of its encoded license bean. License key generators are the product of a call to VendorLicenseManager.generateKeyFrom(License). License key generators are stateful and so they are generally not thread-safe.

    When the license key gets generated, a protective copy of the configured license bean is made which is subsequently initialized and validated.

    Author:
    Christian Schlichtherle
